Class InterpolatingDoubleMap

All Implemented Interfaces:
Serializable, Cloneable, Map<Double,Double>, NavigableMap<Double,Double>, SortedMap<Double,Double>
public class InterpolatingDoubleMap extends TreeMap<Double,Double>
The InterpolatingDoubleMap class is a specialized TreeMap implementation for storing data points as key-value pairs of double values, where the keys represent the independent variable (usually x-values) and the values represent the dependent variable (usually y-values). This class extends the TreeMap class and provides additional functionality for linear interpolation between data points. Linear interpolation is a method for estimating values between two known data points. The class allows you to efficiently perform linear interpolation on the stored data points, enabling you to find interpolated values for a given input independent variable.
